data.text:
Recent news illustrates the passing of Olivia Newton-John.

She was an actress that will prevail with a young image to movie fans.

Olivia Newton-John was the start of Grease, a film known by every generation of movie fanatics.

With John Travolta, Olivia Newton-John transformed a high school love story into one of the most watched films of all time.

Grease is one of the most famous musicals ever written.

Grease was a lifetime movie because of the cars, clothing, cook teens, and catchy songs.

Olivia Newton-John and the characters that immortalized her

Olivia Newton-John was born in Cambridge, UK. Nevertheless, she moved to Melbourne, Australia, with her family at a young age.

She represented the United Kingdom at Eurovision Song Contest in 1974.

Four years later, her life will change forever with Grease.

Olivia Newton-John performed as Sandy Olsson in Grease, and at 28 years old, she became one of the most successful actresses in the world.

Other film and tv projects

Olivia Newton-John's film career ended in 2020.

However, she was part of popular TV Shows such as Saturday Night Live, Timeless Tales from Hallmark, American Idol, Glee, and Dancing with the Stars.

She even had her show and multiple HBO specials.

As a movie actress, she was part of 15 movies.

From 1980 to 2020, Olivia Newton-John participated in Xanadu, Two of a Kind, A mom for Christmas, A Christmas Romance, It's My Party, Sordid Lives, The Wilde Girls, 1 a Minute, Score: A Hockey Musical, A Few Best Men, Sharknado 5, and The Very Excellent Mr. Dundee.
